WEBVTT

00:01.669 --> 00:02.670
[gunshot]

00:02.703 --> 00:03.671
[horse neighs]

00:03.704 --> 00:06.674
[animal snarls]

00:06.707 --> 00:09.043
[man screams]

00:31.265 --> 00:35.569
[whimpering and panting]

00:50.184 --> 00:55.256
[groaning weakly]

00:55.289 --> 00:58.259
[panting]

01:31.259 --> 01:35.263
LORD.

01:35.296 --> 01:37.531
LORD...

01:39.933 --> 01:44.405
DON'T TAKE ME
LIKE THIS.

01:44.438 --> 01:46.574
NOT LIKE THIS.

02:01.922 --> 02:07.895
- [humming]

02:11.632 --> 02:14.635
*

02:32.586 --> 02:34.222
WHO ARE YOU?

02:34.222 --> 02:35.256
[high-pitched whining]

02:35.289 --> 02:36.490
- EVA, IT'S--IT'S ME.

02:38.459 --> 02:40.661
- AAH!

03:41.389 --> 03:44.392
[Western folk music]

03:44.425 --> 03:52.400
*

04:14.455 --> 04:17.758
[high-pitched whining]

04:17.791 --> 04:19.393
[drumming]

04:19.427 --> 04:23.431
[man chanting in Comanche]

04:23.464 --> 04:26.033
*

04:26.066 --> 04:30.571
[speaking in Comanche]

04:37.778 --> 04:41.815
- [stifled groaning]

04:43.617 --> 04:45.586
[chanting and drumming stops]

04:45.619 --> 04:49.690
[stifled groaning]

04:59.132 --> 05:01.802
[panting]

05:14.482 --> 05:17.851
[gurgling]

05:33.701 --> 05:36.770
[man chanting in Comanche]

05:36.804 --> 05:43.811
*

05:43.844 --> 05:48.516
- [speaking Comanche]

06:01.695 --> 06:04.665
[humming]

06:04.698 --> 06:09.703
*

06:18.712 --> 06:21.582
[speaking Comanche]

07:05.926 --> 07:08.729
- [stifled screaming]

07:11.932 --> 07:16.637
- [chanting in Comanche]

07:16.670 --> 07:19.607
[humming]

07:19.640 --> 07:26.980
*

07:28.616 --> 07:31.619
[man chanting in Comanche,
drumming]

07:31.652 --> 07:39.527
*

07:48.301 --> 07:49.770
- FIRE!

07:49.803 --> 07:52.840
FIRE!

07:52.873 --> 07:54.642
MY HOUSE!

07:54.675 --> 07:57.811
FIRE!

07:59.279 --> 08:02.282
[man continues chanting
in Comanche]

08:02.315 --> 08:10.257
*

08:23.637 --> 08:25.839
[dog barks distantly]

08:39.687 --> 08:42.590
- HEY.

09:01.875 --> 09:05.178
[woman making soothing noises]

09:10.918 --> 09:14.988
- [speaking Comanche]

09:15.022 --> 09:18.692
MMM, MMM.
MMM.

09:20.728 --> 09:21.895
MMM.

09:34.041 --> 09:36.710
[speaking Comanche]

09:36.744 --> 09:38.078
HMM.

09:58.732 --> 10:00.768
- [grunts]

10:27.127 --> 10:30.630
[dog barking distantly]

10:32.132 --> 10:35.068
[wind howls]

10:48.048 --> 10:50.951
[fire crackling]

10:50.984 --> 10:53.120
[horse neighs]

10:53.153 --> 10:55.856
[man speaking Comanche]

10:59.126 --> 11:02.262
[woman speaking Comanche]

11:27.154 --> 11:28.989
- GIVE ME THAT MEAT.

11:41.534 --> 11:45.105
I DONE MY WORK.
GIVE ME MY SUPPER.

11:47.841 --> 11:50.043
GIVE ME MY SUPPER.

12:02.055 --> 12:04.491
GIVE ME MY SUPPER!

12:10.530 --> 12:12.232
GIVE ME MY SUPPER!

12:23.543 --> 12:29.049
[people whooping]
[dogs barking]

12:29.082 --> 12:34.154
[horses galloping]
[whooping continues]

12:40.260 --> 12:43.363
[sounds grow distant]

12:53.907 --> 12:56.543
- [grunts]

13:02.549 --> 13:07.921
[men chattering
in Comanche]

13:11.258 --> 13:14.995
[whooping continues]

13:55.035 --> 13:56.103
- [grunts]

13:56.136 --> 13:58.071
[panting]

14:00.273 --> 14:01.909
[grunts]

14:14.221 --> 14:19.326
[wind howling]

14:33.406 --> 14:35.208
- THAT'S MINE.

14:37.377 --> 14:40.347
- [speaking Comanche]

14:43.216 --> 14:45.652
[meat sizzles in fire]

14:58.331 --> 15:03.436
- [speaking Comanche]

15:32.399 --> 15:36.336
[villagers chattering]

16:47.174 --> 16:51.078
- [grunting]

17:58.911 --> 18:02.615
[villagers chattering]

18:15.428 --> 18:16.563
- OH...

18:16.596 --> 18:18.231
AH...

18:18.265 --> 18:22.502
AAH!
[high-pitched whining]

18:22.535 --> 18:24.871
AAH!

18:31.478 --> 18:35.882
DID YOU SEE HER?
DID YOU SEE HER?

18:35.915 --> 18:39.552
WHY'D SHE RUN FROM ME?
WHY'D SHE RUN FROM ME?

18:39.586 --> 18:41.554
SHE WAS SINGING
IN THE FIELD.

18:41.588 --> 18:43.290
[girl gasps]

18:44.457 --> 18:47.427
DID YOU SEE HER?

18:47.460 --> 18:50.263
SHE WAS SINGING
IN THE FIELD.

18:50.297 --> 18:53.566
SHE WAS SINGING IN THE FIELD.

18:53.600 --> 18:56.536
WHY'D SHE RUN AWAY
FROM ME?

19:10.383 --> 19:12.585
[man speaking Comanche]

19:12.619 --> 19:14.687
[shouts in Comanche]

19:19.326 --> 19:21.761
[children giggling]

19:26.399 --> 19:27.634
[thwack]

19:27.667 --> 19:29.236
[wood clatters]

19:31.404 --> 19:33.373
[shouts]

19:33.406 --> 19:35.375
[laughs]

19:47.520 --> 19:49.522
[speaking Comanche]

20:29.429 --> 20:31.664
- NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO.

20:31.698 --> 20:34.501
NO! NO.

20:34.534 --> 20:36.736
OW--PLEASE!

20:38.438 --> 20:40.340
[gasps]

20:40.373 --> 20:43.443
OW.

20:43.476 --> 20:44.611
[grunts]

20:44.644 --> 20:48.047
[panting]

20:48.080 --> 20:49.716
- YOU AIN'T HER.

20:49.749 --> 20:51.684
- WHO?
PLEASE, PLEASE.

20:51.718 --> 20:52.852
MY NAME
IS CHARLOTTE ROYCE!

20:52.885 --> 20:54.521
THE SAVAGES ATTACKED
MY HUSBAND AND ME

20:54.554 --> 20:55.822
ON OUR WAY TO DENVER.

20:55.855 --> 20:58.291
PETER'S DEAD,
BUT HIS BROTHER'S IN CINCINNATI.

20:58.325 --> 21:00.560
IF YOU CAN GET WORD,
HE'LL COME FIND US.

21:00.593 --> 21:03.062
- YOU AIN'T HER.
- NO, NO!

21:03.095 --> 21:05.432
PLEASE! PLEASE!
- YOU AIN'T HER!

21:27.787 --> 21:30.757
[people whooping]

21:30.790 --> 21:33.660
[both grunting]

21:41.634 --> 21:45.705
[high-pitched whining]

21:45.738 --> 21:48.808
- [panting]

21:52.779 --> 21:55.582
[high-pitched whining]

22:09.128 --> 22:12.098
- [grunting]

22:15.535 --> 22:16.803
[whining stops]

22:32.852 --> 22:35.722
[whooping]

22:55.742 --> 22:58.745
[ominous music]

22:58.778 --> 23:06.686
*

23:27.607 --> 23:35.582
*

23:40.920 --> 23:43.890
[mystical music]

23:43.923 --> 23:51.798
*

24:51.824 --> 24:54.927
[mystical music continues]

24:54.961 --> 25:02.869
*

25:39.038 --> 25:42.008
- [speaking Comanche]

25:49.882 --> 25:53.720
[laughter]

26:01.060 --> 26:03.996
- [speaking Comanche]

26:14.073 --> 26:21.948
*

27:18.004 --> 27:19.706
- SOURPUSS?

27:22.041 --> 27:24.376
WELL, LOOKEE HERE.

27:24.410 --> 27:26.746
THEY SAID
THEY FOUND A BEAR KILLER

27:26.779 --> 27:27.980
OUT ON THE PRAIRIE,

27:28.014 --> 27:29.816
BUT IT LOOKS TO ME
LIKE THEY GOT THEMSELVES

27:29.849 --> 27:32.952
A RAILROAD MAN
A LONG WAY FROM HOME.

27:32.985 --> 27:34.420
- WHO IS YOU?

27:34.453 --> 27:37.123
- NOW, DON'T TELL ME
YOU'VE FORGOTTEN OLD JIMMY.

27:37.156 --> 27:39.058
I PULLED YOU
AND THAT MISSISSIPPI BOY

27:39.091 --> 27:41.427
OUT OF THAT TIGHT SPOT
WITH THE KIOWA.

27:41.460 --> 27:44.964
CULLEN BOHANNON
HE SAID HIS NAME WAS.

27:44.997 --> 27:50.937
HAD HIMSELF A SAZERAC ONE TIME
AT THE ST. CHARLES HOTEL.

27:50.970 --> 27:53.139
- BOHANNON?
- THAT'S RIGHT.

27:53.172 --> 27:58.044
WITH THE UNION
PACIFIC RAILROAD.

27:58.077 --> 27:59.111
- I SEE HIM
COVERED IN FLAME.

27:59.145 --> 28:01.013
- OH, THAT'S RIGHT.

28:01.047 --> 28:03.983
NOW, THAT WAS BACK
WITH THE KIOWA.

28:06.018 --> 28:07.754
- BOHANNON SAY
HE FREED THE SLAVES,

28:07.754 --> 28:09.488
BUT HE AIN'T FREE 'EM.

28:09.521 --> 28:13.459
- BOY, WHAT'S INFECTING YOU NOW?

28:15.161 --> 28:19.131
- I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

28:19.165 --> 28:21.000
- NOW, HOLD ON THERE,
SOURPUSS.

28:21.033 --> 28:23.202
LET'S YOU AND ME
FIGURE THIS OUT TOGETHER.

28:30.176 --> 28:31.778
THIS HERE'S
OLD PORCUPINE.

28:31.778 --> 28:33.512
HE'S MY FATHER-IN-LAW.

28:33.545 --> 28:36.182
I COME HERE TO WARN HIM
ABOUT SOME BLUECOATS

28:36.215 --> 28:39.886
I COME ACROSS ABOUT HALF DAY'S
RIDE SOUTH OF HERE.

28:39.919 --> 28:43.856
THEY ON THE WARPATH
LOOKING FOR THAT WHITE WOMAN.

28:43.890 --> 28:45.858
- SHE MINE.

28:45.892 --> 28:48.895
- [laughs]
NO, SHE AIN'T YOURN--

28:48.928 --> 28:51.497
- MARKED UP
WHITE WOMAN MINE.

28:51.530 --> 28:55.101
- MR. LINCOLN MAY HAVE
OUTLAWED SLAVERY IN THE SOUTH,

28:55.134 --> 28:58.037
BUT THESE COMANCHE AIN'T
NEVER HEARD HIS PROCLAMATION.

28:58.070 --> 29:00.206
THAT WHITE WOMAN
IS WHITE FEATHER'S.

29:00.239 --> 29:04.176
SHE WORTH MORE
THAN NEITHER OF US HAS ON US.

29:04.210 --> 29:06.879
- SHE WORTH THREE BLANKETS
AND A HORSE.

29:06.913 --> 29:07.980
THAT'S WHAT SHE SAY.

29:08.014 --> 29:11.183
- THIS--SHE IS WORTH TWICE THAT
AND A BOX OF ROCKS.

29:11.217 --> 29:13.886
WHITE FEATHER
EARNED HER IN BATTLE.

29:13.920 --> 29:18.825
- HE EARNED HER IN BATTLE.
- MM-HMM.

29:18.825 --> 29:21.260
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THEY CALL YOU?

29:21.293 --> 29:24.230
PAH DUH AH
WUH TOH KWEH NUH.

29:24.263 --> 29:27.066
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

29:27.099 --> 29:30.336
"BEAR KILLER."

29:30.369 --> 29:34.240
- PAH DUH AH
WUH TOH KWEH NUH.

29:34.273 --> 29:37.977
- THESE COMANCHE BELIEVE
ANY MAN WHO KILLED A BEAR

29:38.010 --> 29:40.279
TAKES UP ALL HER POWER
AND MAGIC

29:40.312 --> 29:43.249
AND CAN'T BE DEFEATED
IN BATTLE.

29:43.282 --> 29:44.583
IF I KNOW THESE BRAVES,

29:44.616 --> 29:47.086
THEY FIXING TO RIDE
ON THAT CAVALRY TONIGHT,

29:47.119 --> 29:48.220
AND THEY'RE GONNA WANT
BEAR KILLER

29:48.254 --> 29:50.356
AND ALL HIS MAGIC
WITH 'EM.

29:50.389 --> 29:53.392
THEY THINK YOU CAN'T BE KILLED,
BUT I KNOW BETTER.

29:53.425 --> 29:55.261
FACT IS, YOU GONNA FILL UP
FULL OF BULLETS

29:55.294 --> 29:57.196
FASTER THAN ANY OF 'EM
ON ACCOUNT

29:57.229 --> 30:01.100
OF YOU ONLY GOT
ONE GOOD EYE.

30:01.133 --> 30:03.970
AND THAT WHITE WOMAN
IS WHITE FEATHER'S.

30:04.003 --> 30:06.839
YOU GOT A WOMAN
AND A BABY GIRL

30:06.873 --> 30:11.310
BACK IN CHEYENNE.

30:11.343 --> 30:13.980
- HER EYES
WORTH A HUNDRED HORSES.

30:20.052 --> 30:22.188
- WE GOT TO GET YOU BACK THERE
BEFORE YOU LOSE

30:22.221 --> 30:24.290
WHAT'S LEFT OF YOU.

30:27.159 --> 30:30.162
[chanting, whooping]

30:30.196 --> 30:33.199
*

30:39.171 --> 30:41.173
- THIS IS A WAR CEREMONY,

30:41.207 --> 30:43.876
AND THESE BRAVES
IS OUT FOR BLOOD.

30:43.910 --> 30:48.014
IT'S BEST WE GO
BEFORE THEY REALIZE YOU GONE.

30:48.047 --> 30:50.316
WE GOT TO SKEDADDLE,
SOURPUSS.

30:50.349 --> 30:53.052
[all whooping]

30:53.085 --> 30:54.153
COME ON.

30:54.186 --> 30:57.456
[all whooping]

31:19.278 --> 31:23.049
- LOOK, I-I KNOW YOU GOT
YOUR NOGGIN RATTLED REAL GOOD,

31:23.082 --> 31:25.251
BUT--BUT ONCE
YOU SEE YOUR PEOPLE,

31:25.284 --> 31:26.485
WELL, MAYBE YOU'LL START--

31:26.518 --> 31:28.287
- MY NAME IS PAH DUH AH
WUH TOH KWEH NUH.

31:28.320 --> 31:30.156
I GOT MAGIC.
- NO, NO.

31:30.189 --> 31:32.191
YOUR NAME IS ELAM FERGUSON.

31:32.224 --> 31:34.360
YOU A RAILROAD MAN.
YOU GOT A FAMILY.

31:34.393 --> 31:35.995
YOU DON'T BELONG HERE.

31:36.028 --> 31:37.696
- I EARN MY OWN WOMAN
IN BATTLE.

31:37.729 --> 31:40.199
- SON, YOU GO WITH THEM BRAVES,
YOU AIN'T COMING BACK.

31:40.232 --> 31:41.333
NOW, HOLD ON!

31:41.367 --> 31:42.969
YOU AIN'T
IN YOUR RIGHT MIND HERE--

31:42.969 --> 31:45.671
[groaning]

31:53.279 --> 31:56.082
[drumming, whooping continues]

31:56.115 --> 31:59.118
*

34:06.345 --> 34:08.514
- SAVAGES IN THE WOODS!

34:08.547 --> 34:10.549
[gunfire, arrows whistling]
[whooping]

34:10.582 --> 34:12.218
TAKE COVER!

34:14.586 --> 34:16.255
- OH!

34:16.288 --> 34:18.357
GO! GO!

34:18.390 --> 34:20.292
UP HERE!
OVER HERE!

34:25.531 --> 34:28.400
[Comanche whooping]

34:31.470 --> 34:33.205
[indistinct shouting]

34:33.239 --> 34:36.208
[Comanche whooping]

34:36.242 --> 34:37.276
- FALL BACK.

34:37.309 --> 34:40.179
- FALL BACK!

34:40.212 --> 34:41.680
- FALL BACK!

34:46.318 --> 34:47.886
[arrows whistling]

34:47.919 --> 34:48.887
- YAAH!

34:48.920 --> 34:50.422
- AAH!

34:50.456 --> 34:52.524
[gunfire]
- HEAD NORTH!

34:52.558 --> 34:55.394
- HAH! HAH!
- YAH, YAH!

34:59.498 --> 35:04.536
[men whooping]

35:18.584 --> 35:20.419
- YOU'RE A RAILROAD MAN,
RIGHT?

35:20.452 --> 35:21.887
YOU'RE NOT A SAVAGE.
YOU'RE NOT LIKE THEM.

35:21.920 --> 35:26.592
YOU SHOULD BACK THERE
WITH YOUR WIFE AND BABY.

35:26.625 --> 35:28.460
YOU CAN TRADE ME

35:28.494 --> 35:29.695
ON THE RAILROAD.

35:29.728 --> 35:31.697
I'M WORTH MORE
THAN THREE BLANKETS AND A HORSE,

35:31.730 --> 35:34.266
ENOUGH TO GET YOU
TO THAT MARKED UP WHITE WOMAN.

35:34.300 --> 35:39.271
WHAT'S HER NAME?
I KNOW YOU KNOW IT.

35:39.305 --> 35:40.939
- EVA.
- YES!

35:40.972 --> 35:42.241
EVA!

35:42.274 --> 35:43.609
YOU CAN SELL ME
AND GET EVA BACK.

35:43.642 --> 35:44.943
I AM WORTH SOMETHING,

35:44.976 --> 35:46.912
BUT ONLY IF YOU GET ME
OUT OF HERE.

35:52.484 --> 35:54.420
PLEASE, PLEASE.

35:54.453 --> 35:56.488
PLEASE, YOU CAN SELL ME!

35:56.522 --> 35:58.357
YOU CAN SELL ME
AND GET EVA BACK.

35:58.390 --> 36:00.326
PLEASE!
PLEASE, YOU CAN SELL ME!

36:00.359 --> 36:02.328
YOU CAN SELL ME
AND GET EVA BACK!

36:02.361 --> 36:03.929
PLEASE!

36:03.962 --> 36:07.299
NO, YOU CAN SELL ME!

36:07.333 --> 36:10.302
NO!
NO, PLEASE!

36:10.336 --> 36:11.503
NO!

36:11.537 --> 36:14.306
NO, NO!
NO!

36:14.340 --> 36:17.243
[grunting and screaming]

36:19.645 --> 36:22.314
NO! NO!

36:22.348 --> 36:24.650
[panting]

36:24.683 --> 36:27.619
NO! NO!

36:27.653 --> 36:30.522
[panting and grunting]

36:35.594 --> 36:38.464
[woman screaming]

36:53.412 --> 36:55.514
NO! NO!

36:55.547 --> 36:57.749
[whimpering]

37:07.593 --> 37:10.429
[dramatic music]

37:10.462 --> 37:13.465
*

37:29.715 --> 37:32.784
AAH! AAH! AAH!

37:34.553 --> 37:36.788
[panting]

37:40.592 --> 37:44.330
[woman whimpering]

37:57.443 --> 38:00.346
- COME ON.
COME ON!

39:09.715 --> 39:12.684
[thunder rumbles]

40:53.519 --> 40:54.620
- YOU'RE MINE!
- I'M SORRY!

40:54.653 --> 40:55.654
I'M SORRY!

40:55.687 --> 40:56.888
I'M SORRY.
YOU...

40:56.922 --> 40:58.824
- I EARNED YOU.
- KILLED HIM!

40:58.857 --> 41:00.225
YOU KILLED THE TRADER.

41:00.258 --> 41:01.927
HE WAS TRYING TO HELP YOU...
- SHUT UP! SHUT UP!

41:01.960 --> 41:02.794
- AND YOU KILLED HIM!
- SHUT UP!

41:02.828 --> 41:04.262
- YOU'RE WORSE
THAN THE COMANCHE.

41:04.295 --> 41:05.797
YOU'RE AN ANIMAL!
- SHUT UP!

41:05.831 --> 41:07.833
SHUT UP!

41:07.866 --> 41:11.803
SHUT UP!
[woman sobbing]

41:11.837 --> 41:14.840
[bleak music]

41:14.873 --> 41:22.781
*
